Disneyland, California, America 
Disneyland was opened on July 17th, 1955 the theme park operates year-round. Walt Disney came up with the concept of a theme park adjacent to his studios to keep anyone who wanted to visit happy and entertained. Upon realising the venues were too small Walt hired a consultant who helped him look for an appropriate site for the theme-park he ended up buying a 160 acre site in Anaheim California.

Our Mother's Day Competition was a huge success. All entries were special, yet one particular Best Mum nomination touched our heart ❤

With great pleasure we announce that the lucky winner is a real hero mum ... Miriam Zammit! She was nominated by her granddaughter Soawarak Phiram, who shared her story with us. Miriam stepped in to raise and take care of her two grandchildren when their mother sadly passed away. It was a tough yet well-thought choice, a noble gesture which in our opinion deserves recognition. For this reason Miriam, her husband and the two lucky sisters will be flying to a KM destination of their choice, compliments of Air Malta! 
Congratulations Soawarak, thank you for nominating your grandmother and we look forward to contributing to a well-deserved family holiday. 
But that's not all ... we have another winner so watch out for the next post 😉
